rComments: You will not find a prof more helpful and approachable than Prof. Doberstein. His exams were not easy, but also not hard (TAs marked them).  Lectures were entertaining even when the week's topic was a bit boring (this was Canadian politics after all)

One of the best professors I've had in U of T during my 4 years at this school. Very approachable, clearly communicates expectations, does everything possible to ensure you succeed, prepares great notes for you to use during exams. He truly has a gift of teaching that you won't find in older professors, as he truly cares about his students.
Made me interested in Canadian Politics!  Young prof who at least tries to make lectures interesting with short videos and humour.  Approachable, very helpful in office hours.
